bib_record.title: Production of charged pions by 730-MeV protons from hydrogen and selected nuclei

free_txt: Experiment performed at the 184 in.
cyclotron of the Lawrence Radiation Laboratory,
Berkeley
Applied corrections include correction for
- channel-inscattering
- pi-mi decay
- target absorption
- deadtime losses
Reaction products were analyzed in magnetic
spectrometer - a simple dipole C magnet
Set of 4 NE102 scintillation counters  were
used for pion identification. Two scintillators with
thickness of 0.75 mm and 1.5 mm were used to define
primary proton beam.
Third scintillation counter dE was
located at the focal point and defined the momentum
window at given position. Behind third scintillator
a fourth scintillator for pion identification was
placed. Both scintillators were 3mm thick.
Plexiglas Cherenkov counters with thickness
of 2.5 cm were placed behind fourth plastic
scintillator in 6 highest momentum channels to aid
in pion-proton discrimination. Additional methane
gas Cherenkov counter was placed in beam between
first and second plastic to discriminate against
electrons in primary beam.
Total uncertainty, which included
Statistical uncertainty
Systematic uncertainty in beam current
Uncertainty in channel inscattering correction
